# AI Agent Instructions

All project rules live in **.cursor/rules/** (Cursor rule files). Read and follow them.

**Entry point:** .cursor/rules/loader.mdc — lists what to read at the start of every task.

**Rule files:**
- loader.mdc — what to read first (.aidescription, context, requirements; commit-and-devlog; clean-code)
- commit-and-devlog.mdc — before/after every commit (tests, devlog, message, push)
- clean-code.mdc — TDD, atoms (Button/Input/Label), translations, export, minimal change, architecture
- confirmations.mdc — ask before: features not in requirements, new deps, adding to context, large changes
- documentation.mdc — devlog style, where docs live, when to update frontend-tree and architecture
- file-management.mdc — prefer edit over create; no proactive README/docs
- communication.mdc — concise; max 2 questions; track open items in context
- code-standards.mdc — naming, file organization, code quality, design, translations, diagrams

**Reference:** docs/context.txt (Restrictions, Licensing, open conversations), docs/requirements.md (features), docs/design.md (palette). Do not add npm dependencies or implement features outside requirements without asking.
